    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Corbin Carroll** stands alone as the anchor of the lineup with an elite 87.14 score. His massive projection against Germ\u00e1n M\u00e1rquez is bolstered by a 19% SP skill advantage and, crucially for our SB-weighted strategy, M\u00e1rquez\u2019s slow delivery, which grants **Corbin Carroll** a 4% boost in stolen base probability. While **Seiya Suzuki** (68.49) and **Brice Turang** (65.25) also provide high-floor production, **Seiya Suzuki** benefits significantly from a soft matchup against Roki Sasaki (5.52 xERA) combined with favorable wind conditions. **Trevor Story** remains a must-start at 62.07; his output is heavily inflated by a 16% park factor advantage, which mitigates the risk of facing the left-handed Trevor Rogers.\n\nThe decision to bench **Max Muncy** (49.36) was the most difficult call of the morning. While **Max Muncy** holds a respectable projection and a platoon edge against MacKenzie Gore, the optimizer favored the higher lineup placement and superior park factors of **Josh Naylor** (60.52) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (52.95). Furthermore, we are forced to navigate significant volatility: the 36% rain risk at the stadium affects both **Luis Campusano** and **Corbin Carroll**, though the potential for an elite stat line from **Corbin Carroll** makes him impossible to fade. Conversely, **Mickey Moniak** is effectively off the board due to a confirmed postponement, sparing us a bench dilemma. **Austin Riley** was also excluded, as the elite command profile of Zack Wheeler (2.73 xERA) created a prohibitive barrier to entry compared to the softer matchups on tap for **Tyler Soderstrom** and **Alex Freeland**.",
